1
00:00:05,346 --> 00:00:11,816
Sādhu-saṅga leads one
to the association of devotees proper

2
00:00:11,816 --> 00:00:14,746
and then—the most
superior devotee

3
00:00:14,746 --> 00:00:18,586
to put ourselves
under their guidance.

4
00:00:18,826 --> 00:00:21,276
[The First Principle of Vaishnavism]

5
00:00:21,316 --> 00:00:24,006
What’s the first principle
of Vaishnavism?
 

6
00:00:24,006 --> 00:00:26,546
To give up bad association.

7
00:00:26,546 --> 00:00:28,506
Who is bad association? 
 

8
00:00:28,506 --> 00:00:32,726
Anyone who is not seriously 
pursuing Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

9
00:00:33,176 --> 00:00:36,656
That’s how 
it should be understood.

10
00:00:36,656 --> 00:00:41,266
It doesn’t say that people
who are bad association

11
00:00:41,266 --> 00:00:44,406
aren’t nice folks.
[Laughing]

12
00:00:44,406 --> 00:00:46,858
It’s not saying like that.

13
00:00:47,378 --> 00:00:53,878
But they are not seriously 
pursuing Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

14
00:00:55,493 --> 00:00:59,228
Kṛṣṇa-ānuśīlanaṁ,
Kṛṣṇa-ānuśīlanaṁ saṅga—

15
00:00:59,228 --> 00:01:04,468
it’s for those who are serious
about pursuing Kṛṣṇa сonsciousness.

16
00:01:04,839 --> 00:01:07,969
Anartha-nivṛtti,
niṣṭhā—

17
00:01:07,969 --> 00:01:11,119
then faith can become 
deeply rooted

18
00:01:11,119 --> 00:01:14,059
as opposed 
to a superficial embrace,

19
00:01:14,059 --> 00:01:16,329
spiritual tourism.

20
00:01:17,129 --> 00:01:19,759
Niṣṭhā—
like when a plant takes root,

21
00:01:19,759 --> 00:01:22,679
we’re talking about seed,
follow that example.

22
00:01:22,679 --> 00:01:24,499
You know, when 
you have a little plant.

23
00:01:24,499 --> 00:01:28,729
What do they call when you put all
the little plants in a special room?

24
00:01:28,729 --> 00:01:32,279
It’s called “a nursery” in English.

25
00:01:32,589 --> 00:01:34,939
Same thing like 
where you put babies

26
00:01:34,939 --> 00:01:37,159
is what they use for plants.

27
00:01:37,159 --> 00:01:39,609
Because they know—
these little baby-plants,

28
00:01:39,609 --> 00:01:42,929
they can’t survive
in the environment.

29
00:01:42,929 --> 00:01:46,419
That’s why you need 
spiritual association,

30
00:01:46,419 --> 00:01:49,299
and be surrounded
by devotees.

31
00:01:49,299 --> 00:01:53,469
Pull little baby—
bhakti-latā-bīj, bhakti-latā—

32
00:01:53,469 --> 00:01:55,749
out of the association 
of devotees

33
00:01:55,749 --> 00:02:01,069
and put them in an environment 
surrounded by non-devotees—

34
00:02:01,069 --> 00:02:03,479
they will not survive.

35
00:02:04,077 --> 00:02:08,317
Their Kṛṣṇa conception
will go into dormancy.

36
00:02:13,914 --> 00:02:17,124
Sādhu-saṅga satovare—

37
00:02:17,124 --> 00:02:21,784
we need to surround ourselves
with good association,

38
00:02:21,784 --> 00:02:24,934
and that means like …

39
00:02:25,459 --> 00:02:30,749
When we were climbing 
the mountains with my friends,

40
00:02:30,787 --> 00:02:37,206
we went from Rishikesh, Haridvar 
to Badrinath climbing a mountain.

41
00:02:37,206 --> 00:02:40,776
Sometimes one person
wants to give up,

42
00:02:41,196 --> 00:02:44,076
“I can’t take another step.”

43
00:02:44,327 --> 00:02:49,347
But another person 
who’s got their wind and …

44
00:02:49,347 --> 00:02:55,309
who said, “Oh, we’re so close
to the next chatthi or the next stop. 
 

45
00:02:55,309 --> 00:02:58,312
Don’t stop now!
Come on with me!”

46
00:02:58,972 --> 00:03:01,772
On the basis of their encouragement
and enthusiasm they say,

47
00:03:01,772 --> 00:03:05,292
“Alright! I’ll go a little bit further.”
Then going a little bit further,

48
00:03:05,292 --> 00:03:09,292
“Oh, I’m getting my second wind,
I feel some strength coming back.”

49
00:03:09,292 --> 00:03:13,412
The other person, “Good!
Because now I’m feeling discouraged.”

50
00:03:13,952 --> 00:03:15,682
That’s why we need association.

